Title: Antiferromagnetic S=1/2 Heisenberg Chain and the Two-flavor Massless
  Schwinger Model
Authors: Yutaka Hosotani
Comments: 3 pages. LaTex2e
Report-no: UMN-TH-1717/98
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Statistical Mechanics
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. B60 (1999) 6198-6199
\\
  An antiferromagnetic S=1/2 Heisenberg chain is mapped to the two-flavor
massless Schwinger model at \theta=\pi. The electromagnetic coupling constant
and velocity of light in the Schwinger model are determined in terms of the
Heisenberg coupling and lattice spacing in the spin chain system.
